From: Rolando Trevino <rolo@trevino.dev>
Subject: [PATCH] ALSA: usb-audio: Add fixed-rate quirk for Universal Audio USB devices

Universal Audio Apollo Solo USB, Twin USB, and Twin X USB devices
use a Cypress FX3 USB controller with a custom FPGA backend. Their
UAC2 clock source does not implement the GET_RANGE request for
sample rate enumeration (returns STALL), which prevents
snd-usb-audio from creating PCM streams.

These devices support 48kHz fixed sample rate. Add them to the
existing fixed-rate quirk table alongside Line6 and Rode devices
that have the same limitation.

Tested with Universal Audio Apollo Solo USB (VID 0x2b5a, PID 0x000d)
on Linux 6.17.0 — device correctly enumerates playback (6ch) and
capture (10ch) PCM streams after this patch.

Signed-off-by: Rolando Trevino <rolo@trevino.dev>
---
 sound/usb/format.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/sound/usb/format.c b/sound/usb/format.c
index XXXXXXX..XXXXXXX 100644
--- a/sound/usb/format.c
+++ b/sound/usb/format.c
@@ -435,6 +435,9 @@ static int line6_parse_audio_format_rates_quirk(struct snd_usb_audio *chip,
 	case USB_ID(0x0e41, 0x424b): /* Line6 Pod Go */
 	case USB_ID(0x19f7, 0x0011): /* Rode Rodecaster Pro */
 		return set_fixed_rate(fp, 48000, SNDRV_PCM_RATE_48000);
+	case USB_ID(0x2b5a, 0x000d): /* Universal Audio Apollo Solo USB */
+	case USB_ID(0x2b5a, 0x0002): /* Universal Audio Twin USB */
+	case USB_ID(0x2b5a, 0x000f): /* Universal Audio Twin X USB */
+		return set_fixed_rate(fp, 48000, SNDRV_PCM_RATE_48000);
 	}

 	return -ENODEV;
--
2.43.0
